    <div class="body">
        <p>I have noticed that Zend_Locale throws an exception with the message "Autodetection of Locale has been failed!" when used with Zend_Rest_Server and Zend_Rest_Client.</p>

<p>Here is my setup...</p>

<p>Server A
- Zend_Rest_Server instance.
- Exception thrown when using $date = new Zend_Date(); within a rest controller.</p>

<p>Server B
- Zend_Rest_Client initiates request to Server A.</p>

<p>I have also noticed this problem with visitors to my site.  It is infrequent but a real bug that is causing some browsers to die when the exception is thrown.</p>

